        <abstract>
            <p>Spoke too harshly about CD’s involvement in nomenclatural reform.</p>
            <p>JDH used to think CD "too prone to theoretical considerations about species", hence was pleased CD took up a difficult group like barnacles. CD’s theories have progressed but JDH not converted. Sikkim has not cleared up his doubts about CD’s doctrines.</p>
            <p>Argument with Falconer.</p>
        </abstract>
